A lot of people were asking and wondering why I was sitting out and not playing keyboards and organ on Sundays for so long. I was assigned to and going through a much needed and very intentional restoration process. I’m so much better because of it and I’m thankful for a pastor and a church that believes in building and restoring people beyond their gift and contribution. This is what discipleship is all about. I’m grateful to be able to be on a platform but if it never happened again I’m even more grateful for the opportunity to grow and become better. I’m grateful for every opportunity! None is ever or will ever be taken for granted. I will be a living story. My life is my testimony, ❤️.

I just want to take time to appreciate my father. My father to me is the greatest man in the world. Second to none. Thank you dad for being who you are to me. Always being here for me in every season. Giving me sound direction, instruction and counsel. Thank you for raising me in the Word and teaching me how to be a man. I can’t put into words how much I appreciate and love you. You always taught me right and even when I didn’t understand or didn’t listen, you never gave up on me. I’m grateful that you’re my dad! Love you dad.
I never knew that I could ever love anyone this much. I can’t believe I’m a dad. Im grateful I’m her dad. ❤️ WLM

Moment of transparency: I wrote this verse when I found out baby Willow was on the way. I wrote a lot during that time. There’s so much from this season that I want to share with you all. For every season you find yourself in there purpose attached to it. You can’t run from it even if you tried.

Share this with someone.

21 Days with Jesus. Day 2

Moral of the story is if you’re a musician, you should always be in place. 😂🤦🏾‍♂️ You never know when you’re gonna get called. Pastor lovingly tells my why I need to be in place. 

This was a great point to be in place for. Knowing that I’m still called and it’s not based on anything that I have done or haven’t done. He calls me in-spite of me! God is amazing!

We Are Called Regardless of Our Failures - 2 Tim. 1:8-11

Forgiveness. 
Who are we fighting? 
It’s never them. 
We’re all given the same amount of grace. 

Matthew 5:43-48
Colossians 3:13 
Ephesians 6:12
Ephesians 4:7 

Please share with someone who needs to hear.

Thank you to my friend @kitkatoncg for helping me see this. ❤️

21 days with Jesus Day 4! 

All my baby knows is that while I’m holding her, she’s safe. 
Psalms 91:2 

Share this with someone.

21 days with Jesus 
Day 5
Your thorn is necessary!! 

We may want it to be removed but it may be what God is using for you to trust him even more. 

2 Corinthians 12:7-10
So to keep me from becoming proud, I was given a thorn in my flesh, a messenger from Satan to torment me and keep me from becoming proud.

Three different times I begged the Lord to take it away. Each time he said, “My grace is all you need. My power works best in weakness.” So now I am glad to boast about my weaknesses, so that the power of Christ can work through me. That’s why I take pleasure in my weaknesses, and in the insults, hardships, persecutions, and troubles that I suffer for Christ. For when I am weak, then I am strong.

We are 4 days away from the release of LEAVE IT ALL BEHIND!! 

I promise you that there isn’t a more perfect time to release this song than now. I wrote it in 2019, recorded it in 2020, music video in 2021 and now we’re releasing it in 2023. This is just the beginning of the journey I’m on and on I’m excited to be in the position to invite you guys on it with me. This is just the beginning. I want even people sing this song, they get that thing on their mind that they’re leaving behind and really leave it. ITS NOT MY PROBLEM ANYMORE!!!! It’s that simple. God wants so much more for you, so why forgot the blessing that are ahead because you can’t let go of what is behind you? I cannot wait to sing this all over the world. I can’t wait to hear you guys sing this and declare that you’re leaving it all behind. Let’s go!!

Let me introduce you to the band. TOMORROW LEAVE IT ALL BEHIND DROPS. I hope you preordered already. 

I’ll be sharing videos of the process! Can’t wait to do more!

My baby was dedicated today! I’m so grateful to God that she’s here. God gave her to me and her mom and today we made a commitment publicly to raise her under the influence of the Holy Spirit. She doesn’t belong to me. She belongs to God and He made me responsible for her. I love my baby so much and I’m grateful for the honor to be her father. I’m not striving for her to see me as a great dad, or even the best dad. This isnt about me at all. The only thing I want her to see me as is always here. Her being here changed my life she I would go as far as saying that she saved my life. Thank you Willow for pulling a love out of me that I never knew existed. Thank you for showing me that patience and selflessness was something that I had inside of me on this level. Thank you for giving me even more reason to walk in my purpose even harder. Thank you for giving me more reason to walk boldly in the things of God. He knew what He was doing the whole time. He used you to change me! I promise I won’t let you down baby. Thank you to all of family and friends that came to support on both sides. Her village is massive and I’m grateful for that as well. Willow Love McMillan you are here and I’m grateful.❤️
